# .env.example тЖФ .env sync

When you **add, rename, or change the default** of any variable in a `.env.example` file,
update the matching **`.env`** in the **same directory** in the same change.

## Layout

| `.env.example` | Mirror to |
|---|---|
| `.env.example` (repo root) | `.env` (repo root) |
| `apps/engine/.env.example` | `apps/engine/.env` |
| `apps/api/.env.example` | `apps/api/.env` |
| `apps/web/.env.example` | `apps/web/.env` |

`uv run` in `apps/engine` loads `apps/engine/.env`; Compose and Node often use the root `.env`.
When a variable is shared across services, update **both** the component `.env.example` and the
root `.env.example`, then mirror each to its `.env`.

## Rules

- **Add missing keys** to `.env` with the same placeholder/default as `.env.example`.
- **Do not overwrite** existing secret values in `.env` (passwords, `TOKEN_ENC_KEY`, `JWT_SECRET`, `HF_TOKEN`, etc.) тАФ only add the key or update documented non-secret defaults when intentionally changing the default.
- **Never commit** `.env` files.
- **Do not read or print** `.env` contents in chat or logs.

## Engine tuning defaults

For `apps/engine`, standard tuning defaults (retrieval weights, timeouts, worker timings, etc.)
live in `apps/engine/src/config/constants.py`, **not** `.env.example` тАФ see `engine-config.mdc`. This
sync rule applies only to keys that legitimately belong in `.env.example` (connections, secrets,
endpoints, model ids, cross-service contracts, and feature toggles).

## Definition of Done

A config change is incomplete until every touched `.env.example` has its sibling `.env` updated.
